White Nf5 is also loose, even though it is on a great square.

White resigned here, I think prematurely.  Black can play Ne7, but White can defend with Ne3, avoiding the loss of a piece.  Black can gain a pawn with Nxh4, but I don't think White's game is lost.  On the contrary, White has more space and better pieces.  Perhaps I am missing something, but I was surprised by the win.
